Extract two magic-value string literals into well-named constants:

1. **`"application/octet-stream"` in `Controllers/FilesController.cs`** — The Download endpoint hardcodes this as the fallback content type when `TryGetContentType` returns false. Extract to a `private const string DefaultContentType = "application/octet-stream";` at the top of the `FilesController` class, and reference it in both the XML doc comment and the ternary expression.

2. **`"FileService"` config section name in `Program.cs`** — The section name is passed as a raw string to `builder.Configuration.GetSection("FileService")`. Extract to a `const string FileServiceSectionName = "FileService";` at the top of the `Program` class, and reference it in the `GetSection` call. Also consider adding the same constant to `Configuration/FileServiceOptions.cs` as a `public const string SectionName = "FileService";` and referencing it from Program.cs (preferred: put it on the options class since that's where the section binding is conceptually owned).

Do NOT change any behavior. Only extract the literals to named constants with brief doc comments.

Verification: Run `dotnet build TestProject.sln` and `dotnet test TestProject.sln`. Confirm all tests pass.

